            GAMSAT
            / %sup ®
            Section 2 Essay Length
          %p
            ACER does not provide any guidelines in regards to a minimum word count, or how long your Section 2 essays should be. However, a maxim that holds true even for the GAMSAT
            %sup ®
            Exam is Quality over Quantity.
          %p
            The quality of what you write is much more important than the quantity and as such, you should focus on what you write about and your expression and organisation of ideas. A good guideline is to aim for:
          .diffr_country
            %ul.cstm_list_style
              %li.mtop_zero An Introduction
              %li.mtop_zero 3 Body Paragraphs
              %li.mtop_zero A Conclusion
          %p
            Note however that this example structure is not necessarily applicable to every type of essay. If you were to write a creative piece, the structure of your GAMSAT
            %sup ®
            essay could certainly be more flexible. The main factor to take into account is how best to organise your ideas to ensure that your arguments are conveyed logically and coherently.
          %p
            A common piece of advice is to aim for about 500 words, but the most important point is to focus on the quality of your essay rather than the quantity. If you can express an idea clearly and effectively in less words then do it.
