                %b Plan Body Paragraphs Thematically
              %p Using those ideas that you came up with in brainstorm, plan a number of ‘topic sentences’ that form the main idea for each paragraph, or chunk of writing, in your piece. Each paragraph should address one idea only and should be directly related to the thesis. Each idea should continue to build and extend the thesis, convincing and compelling the reader of your overall contention (opinion) on the issue.
              %p On the big day, planning your essay should take no longer than five minutes. Practice makes perfect, and most importantly, improves your speed.

